The acronym VM stand for?
Ans:virtual machine

What tool do we use to interact with the operating system? 
Ans:terminal

What service do we use to form our VPN connection into HTB labs?
Ans:openvpn
[OpenVPN is an open-source VPN protocol that makes use of virtual private network (VPN) techniques to establish safe site-to-site or point-to-point connections.]

What tool do we use to test our connection to the target with an ICMP echo request?
Ans:ping
[Ping (Packet Internet Groper) which uses ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) to reports errors and provides information related to IP packet processing.
Ping command additionally provides information about a network performance, a round-trip time, a time to send an ICMP request packet and receive an ICMP reply packet.]

What is the name of the most common tool for finding open ports on a target?
Ans:nmap
[Nmap (Network Mapper) is a free and open-source tool for network discovery and security auditing. Sometimes can not find out open ports. We can try $nmap -Pn (IP).]

What service do we identify on port 23/tcp during our scans?
Ans:telnet
[TELNET (TErminaL NETwork) is a type of protocol that enables one computer to connect to local computer.
It follows TCP/IP networking protocol for creating remote sessions. Telnet is not a secure protocol and is unencrypted.]
-----
Using telnet tool enter to that machine #telnet (IP).
Therefore, you need to login in Meow machine. (username is root typically.)
Finally, you will input $ls to find out all documents, and using $cat tool to see the content of flag.txt.
